The paper discusses the use of automatic image processing, computer vision, and learning algorithms for analyzing video data produced by VCE exams. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for polyp detection, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges faced by standard image processing methods, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the unique imaging characteristics of VCE, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of learning algorithms for polyp detection, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
